tartup%20SuppCo%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Martocci%2C%20GroupMe%20and%20Splice%20cofounder%2C%20and%20now%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20SuppCo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670fcda7a70318649282cf32%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESuppCo%20is%20Steve%20Martocci's%20latest%20consumer%20business%2C%20following%20successful%20brands%20such%20as%20GroupMe%20and%20Splice.%3Cp%3ESuppCo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESteve%20Martocci%2C%20cofounder%20of%20GroupMe%2C%20Blade%2C%20and%20Splice%2C%20is%20back%20with%20a%20new%20consumer%20health%20app.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20startup%2C%20SuppCo%2C%20helps%20people%20find%20trusted%20supplements%20and%20track%20their%20health%20progress.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20startup%20just%20raised%20%245.5%20million%20in%20seed%20funding%20from%20Union%20Square%20Ventures%20and%20True%20Ventures.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Steve%20Martocci%20was%20still%20living%20in%20New%20York%2C%20the%20then-29-year-old%20GroupMe%20cofounder%20wanted%20to%20plan%20a%20date%20at%20the%20ultra-exclusive%20speakeasy%20Please%20Don't%20Tell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20a%20reservation%20at%20Please%20Don't%20Tell%20was%20no%20easy%20feat.%20New%20Yorkers%20hoping%20to%20sip%20cocktails%20at%20the%20East%20Village%20joint%20hidden%20behind%20a%20phone%20booth%20had%20to%20call%20right%20as%20the%20bar%20opened%2C%20and%20beat%20out%20the%20others%20doing%20the%20same%2C%20for%20any%20chance%20at%20a%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartocci%20decided%20to%20solve%20his%20problem%20with%20code.%20He%20wrote%20a%20script%20that%20created%20dozens%20of%20phone%20numbers%20to%20call%20the%20bar's%20reception%20and%20then%20converge%20those%20lines%20into%20a%20conference%20call%20when%20an%20employee%20picked%20up%20one%20of%20the%20calls.%20His%20plan%20worked%20%E2%80%94%20he%20got%20the%20reservation%2C%20and%20then%20shared%20the%20application%20around%20to%20his%20friends%20for%20good%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20only%20work%20on%20things%20that%20I%20really%20want%20to%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20laughed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20same%20approach%20he's%20applied%20to%20the%20past%20three%20companies%20he's%20started%3A%20GroupMe%2C%20Blade%2C%20and%20Splice.%20GroupMe%2C%20which%20he%20built%20in%20TechCrunch%20Disrupt's%2024-hour%20hackathon%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-groupme%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esold%20to%20Skype%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20year%20after%20its%20creation%20for%20%2485%20million%20when%20Martocci%20was%2027.%20His%20second%20company%2C%20music%20production%20platform%20Splice%2C%20where%20Martocci%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarting-up-interview-steve-martocci-founder-of-groupme-blade-splice-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espent%20eight%20years%20as%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20raised%20%24160%20million%20in%20venture%20capital%2C%20according%20to%20PitchBook.%20He%20also%20helped%20build%20the%20helicopter%20taxi%20company%20Blade%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fipo-edge.com%2Fblade-completes-business-combination-becoming-the-first-publicly-traded-urban-air-mobility-company%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewent%20public%20in%202021.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%2C%20at%20a%20dinner%20party%2C%20Martocci's%20friend%20said%20she'd%20spent%20four%20hours%20that%20day%20organizing%20her%20supplements%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0after%20Martocci%20had%20been%20struggling%20with%20his%20own%20health%20and%20building%20up%20a%20corresponding%20supplement%20routine%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0his%20wheels%20started%20spinning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Martocci%20is%20unveiling%20his%20latest%20venture%3A%20an%20app%20that%20helps%20people%20find%20consumer-trusted%20supplements%2C%20create%20and